y, and the relations between them, with the priory providing schools, hospitals, chantries and regular sermons, but also acting as a disciplinary force. On a wider level, she also looks at the whole question of lay religion andwhat can be discovered about it. She finishes by an examination of local reactions to the Reformation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aChantriesxEnglandxDurham. 0aChantrieszEnglandzDurham. 0aChurch managementxEnglandxDurhamxHistory, 16th century. 0aChurch managementxEnglandxDurhamxHistory, To 1500. 0aChurch managementzEnglandzDurhamxHistoryy16th century. 0aChurch managementzEnglandzDurhamxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aLaityxEnglandxDurhamxHistory, 16th century. 0aLaityxEnglandxDurhamxHistory, To 1500. 0aLaityzEnglandzDurhamxHistoryy16th century. 0aLaityzEnglandzDurhamxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aParishesxEnglandxDurhamxHistory, 16th century. 0aParishesxEnglandxDurhamxHistory, To 1500. 0aParisheszEnglandzDurhamxHistoryy16th century. 0aParisheszEnglandzDurhamxHistoryyTo 1500. 4aHistory of Religion. 4aMedieval History. 7aRELIGION / History.2bisacsh  aMedieval Durham.  aParish history.  aReformation.  aReligious life.1 aHarvey, Margaret M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013z978311143139040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781846154829?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781846154829423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781846154829/original  a978-3-11-143139-0  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013b2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles